1. Whitespaces
===============
public void
(a + b)
java is free-form language..it means no Special indetion is required.

2. Identifiers
===============
words to declare a class/method/variable

identifiers can be of uppercase, lowercase, toggleCase,underscores, $, numeric
it should start with numbers
java CASE SENSITIVE... student != Student

3. Comments
=============
//single line coments
/*
multiline comments
*/

/**
*Documents comment
*
*/

4.Separators
==============
[] , {} , comma, ;, .

5. Java keyword
================
50 keywords
2 reserved words (const,goto) but not used
3 literals not keywords (true,false,null)


Naming Convention
==================
1. class names can be any NOUN starting with Uppercase letter. eg. Student
2. variable and package names should with lowercase letter eg. git
3. method names  can be any verb starting with lowercase letter eg. show, get, display
4. interface any Adjective staring with Uppercase eg. Runnable

Escape sequence
==================
tab,new line, " , ', octal or hexadecimal [\t,\n,\b,\",\`,\ddd,\uxxxx]

Java Type Conversion
=======================
for automatic type conversion

the two types should be compatible AND
the destination type should be larger than the source type

int a = byte b;   possible because (int>byte)


ARRAY
=======
group of similar type of variables; refered by a common variable name/identifier

1-Dimensional array
====================
type vaiablename[] = new type[size];

int rahul[] = new int[20]; // it will create integer typed array of 2 element capacity and will be referred by the name rahul.

2-D/Multidimensional Array
type vaiablename[][] = new type[rowSize][colSize];

int satya[][] = new int[2][3]; //it will create integer typed array of 2 rows and 3 columns an will be referred by the identifier satya

Array accessing can be done on the basis of index value.
index starts with 0.




 